    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Queen : It's a Kinda Magic"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>From Australia, the most spectacular tribute show to the band Queen is stopping off for its first tour of Quebec's biggest cities.</p>\n\n<p>See this ultimate celebration of the famous British band, which has been touring the world for years, live on stage. A mega-production with state-of-the-art sound, lighting, and projections, featuring not only their stage costumes, but also the band's greatest hits, including <i>Bohemian Rhapsody</i>, <i>We Will Rock You</i>, <i>We Are the Champions</i>, <i>Radio GaGa</i>, <i>I Want to Break Free</i>, <i>Somebody to Love</i>, <i>Don't Stop Me Now</i>, <i>Another One Bites the Dust</i> et plusieurs autres.</p>\n\n<p>\nStarring Warren Vernon-Driscoll, who in his role as Freddie Mercury not only reprises the icon's vocal performances in the original keys, but also plays the musical scores on guitar and piano originally performed by Freddie Mercury. He is accompanied on stage by a group of outstanding musicians reprising the roles of John Deacon, Roger Taylor, and Brian May.</p>\n\n<iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/7KaifBdlhYE?si=6UwSDuiD201asIFG' title='YouTube video player' frameborder='0' allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share' referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
